newsitem.title: NETHERLANDS: NWE products steady to weak after IPE sell-off.
newsitem.headline: NWE products steady to weak after IPE sell-off.

text.p: NWE oil products were steady to weak on Thursday morning after the sell-off of crude futures late on Wednesday, dealers said.
Gasoline barges were likely to be offered at $206 fob ARA, with some trader interest, but little end-user demand.
Heating oil barges dipped as gas oil futures slipped 50 cents. A 2,000 tonne lot traded at IPE Sept +25 cents fob Antwerp. Rotterdam material was about 50 cents higher.
Fuel oil was down $1 from late Wednesday levels, trading twice at $98 fob ARA.
